Bill from greece!

In the `errors` module create an `AbortException` class that is a derived class of `RuntimeError`, then create a series of subclasses such as `APDUTooLong`, `ApplicationExceededReplyTime`, `BufferOverflow`, and the others.  When any of these exceptions are raised during the interpretation of an APDU then trap it and return an `AbortPDU` to the client with the appropriate reason code.

Similarly, create a `RejectException` class with subclass for `InconsistentParameters`, `InvalidParameterDataType`, `InvalidTag`, and the others.  Trap these and return a `RejectPDU` to the client.

Note that BUFFER_OVERFLOW and OTHER are identical names, so call these `AbortBufferOverflow` and `RejectBufferOverflow`.  Putting the Abort and Reject prefix in front of all of the exceptions is superfluous.

